ingredients: 7 small baking potatoes, peeled and sliced
1 (16 oz) package frozen mixed vegetables, thawed
1 (10.75 oz) can condensed cream of mushroom soup
instructions: Stir mixed vegetables and condensed soup in a bowl.
Boil sliced potatoes in water until tender, then drain.
Cook ground beef in skillet over medium-high heat until browned, breaking up lumps.
Drain grease from beef and spread in 9×13 inch baking dish.
Pour vegetable and soup mixture over beef.
Arrange cooked potato slices over vegetables.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes until cheese is melted and dish is bubbly.
